{
  "texts": [
    "We fine-tuned these models on our dataset for the NLI task to test the hypothesis if models trained to understand numbers better aid in verifying numerical claims.",
    "All models are fine-tuned with hyperparameters described in Section 4.2.",
    "Automated Analysis of Quality of decompositionExamining questions generated by ClaimDecomp and Program-FC, we prioritize their relevance to the original claim and diversity in covering different claim aspects.",
    "Score [58] is employed to assess relevance, i.e., measuring how well the questions align with the claims.",
    "For diversity, which ensures non-redundancy and coverage of various claim facets, we utilize the sum of (1-BLEU) and Word Position Deviation [23]."
  ]
}